WEBVTT

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:58.622
INSURANCE PAYOUT STATEMENT

00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:02.167
You knew your parents took out
life insurance policies, didn't you?

00:01:04.086 --> 00:01:06.463
You were at the scene that day
and were the only survivor.

00:01:09.550 --> 00:01:10.718
You're the only one…

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:14.054
who knows the truth.

00:01:17.766 --> 00:01:19.268
Who started the fire?

00:01:24.023 --> 00:01:24.899
Don't tell me…

00:01:26.901 --> 00:01:27.735
That's right.

00:01:32.823 --> 00:01:33.908
It was me.

00:01:36.452 --> 00:01:37.661
I killed them.

00:02:20.871 --> 00:02:22.623
Tell me exactly what happened.

00:02:23.123 --> 00:02:24.625
I killed my parents

00:02:25.542 --> 00:02:27.169
to get the insurance payout.

00:02:30.047 --> 00:02:31.924
What? Is that not a good enough answer?

00:02:33.008 --> 00:02:35.427
I got those men to take out policies too,
but it didn't work out.

00:02:35.511 --> 00:02:36.387
I killed all of them.

00:02:36.470 --> 00:02:38.180
Did you really do it?!

00:02:39.473 --> 00:02:41.183
That's what you wanted to hear.

00:02:42.101 --> 00:02:43.310
Tell me the truth.

00:02:46.105 --> 00:02:46.939
The truth?

00:02:50.192 --> 00:02:51.860
I've always spoken the truth.

00:02:53.946 --> 00:02:57.032
You're the one who won't believe me.

00:03:25.185 --> 00:03:26.061
I'm curious.

00:03:26.979 --> 00:03:30.107
If the secret you've been hiding
is out in the open,

00:03:30.607 --> 00:03:32.192
would you still be so composed?

00:03:33.152 --> 00:03:35.571
How long are you going
to keep defending Ms. Han?

00:03:36.071 --> 00:03:39.658
I'm losing face in front of the staff.

00:03:39.742 --> 00:03:41.452
She's important to me.

00:03:41.535 --> 00:03:43.912
Every shadow needs light

00:03:43.996 --> 00:03:45.497
to maintain balance.

00:03:46.457 --> 00:03:47.374
Chair Kim.

00:03:47.875 --> 00:03:50.461
I heard a story that gave me chills.

00:03:51.295 --> 00:03:52.421
Apparently, Ms. Han…

00:03:54.131 --> 00:03:57.801
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

00:03:58.469 --> 00:04:00.763
Do you know what insurance scammers
have in common?

00:04:01.555 --> 00:04:03.599
Once they've had a taste of money,
they want more.

00:04:04.308 --> 00:04:05.976
What is it that you really want to know?

00:04:07.352 --> 00:04:08.395
Your fiancé

00:04:09.813 --> 00:04:10.856
and Kim Yun-ji.

00:04:12.357 --> 00:04:13.317
Did you kill them?

00:04:16.320 --> 00:04:17.571
You're the only one

00:04:18.655 --> 00:04:19.782
who knows the truth.

00:04:35.631 --> 00:04:37.966
This is when
detective experience pays off, huh?

00:04:38.926 --> 00:04:42.262
If your gut tells you something's wrong,
there's always a reason.

00:04:43.347 --> 00:04:44.807
You've dealt with enough cases
to know the signs.

00:04:49.853 --> 00:04:51.480
What's the problem?

00:04:52.689 --> 00:04:55.692
You should be excited
about uncovering evidence.

00:04:56.652 --> 00:04:58.612
Has that experience ever failed you?

00:05:00.948 --> 00:05:02.199
Or did you ever want it to be wrong?

00:05:02.991 --> 00:05:03.867
What?

00:05:05.410 --> 00:05:06.411
Don't tell me

00:05:06.495 --> 00:05:08.413
you still believe her?

00:05:11.166 --> 00:05:13.627
You've got to be kidding me!

00:05:30.811 --> 00:05:31.645
By the way…

00:05:34.439 --> 00:05:36.692
why did you stay by my side back then?

00:05:38.861 --> 00:05:39.820
When we were kids,

00:05:39.903 --> 00:05:43.031
no one would sit next to me
because they said I smelled like smoke.

00:05:44.158 --> 00:05:47.619
But whenever I went to the cafeteria,
you were always waiting for me.

00:05:49.538 --> 00:05:52.291
You'd sit across from me and eat with me.

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:54.084
That's how

00:05:55.127 --> 00:05:56.628
I found the courage…

00:05:58.463 --> 00:06:00.632
to go back to school each day.

00:06:03.260 --> 00:06:04.803
It wasn't our fault, you know.

00:06:07.055 --> 00:06:10.142
I think that was the day
when it all started.

00:06:12.019 --> 00:06:13.979
Go find your mother.

00:06:14.563 --> 00:06:17.024
Find her and bring her back,
you little bastard!

00:06:18.400 --> 00:06:21.069
She said she was going out to make sales,

00:06:21.945 --> 00:06:24.239
but then she threw me away
like I was garbage.

00:06:24.823 --> 00:06:28.243
You're just like your mother,

00:06:28.327 --> 00:06:29.912
you ungrateful bastard.

00:06:30.412 --> 00:06:32.164
You little shit.

00:06:32.873 --> 00:06:34.124
Why you…

00:06:34.208 --> 00:06:35.167
You punk!

00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:36.335
Come here. You're dead.

00:06:37.586 --> 00:06:38.921
Eun-hye, run.

00:06:39.755 --> 00:06:40.756
-Get over here!
-Go, Eun-hye.

00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:42.341
You little bastard!

00:06:51.099 --> 00:06:52.100
You bastard.

00:06:53.227 --> 00:06:54.353
Damn you!

00:06:55.520 --> 00:06:56.480
Dad!

00:06:57.940 --> 00:06:59.566
Dad!

00:06:59.650 --> 00:07:00.484
Dad…

00:07:12.913 --> 00:07:13.872
Do Eun-hyuk, get up.

00:07:40.607 --> 00:07:41.650
Here, try this.

00:07:43.443 --> 00:07:44.736
Slow down.

00:07:47.072 --> 00:07:47.906
Here you go.

00:07:51.201 --> 00:07:52.703
Goodness, you eat so well.

00:07:59.876 --> 00:08:01.128
Stay still.

00:08:10.137 --> 00:08:12.848
I realized for the first time that night…

00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:18.061
what it feels like
to have someone by my side.

00:08:20.522 --> 00:08:22.649
I still got hit just as badly,
but it hurt less,

00:08:23.191 --> 00:08:24.276
and I could endure it.

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:26.653
I could keep living.

00:08:27.738 --> 00:08:31.908
No one gets to pick their parents
before they're born.

00:08:32.784 --> 00:08:33.785
So it wasn't our fault.

00:08:36.079 --> 00:08:37.205
Not yours, not mine.

00:08:38.332 --> 00:08:39.791
It wasn't my fault?

00:08:40.751 --> 00:08:43.462
It wasn't your fault
that your house caught on fire that day.

00:08:50.469 --> 00:08:52.971
I know you feel guilty
for surviving alone.

00:08:54.890 --> 00:08:55.974
But you have to let it go.

00:08:57.601 --> 00:08:58.602
That's enough.

00:09:04.316 --> 00:09:05.525
Stop drinking.

00:09:05.609 --> 00:09:07.736
Why do you two keep drinking
on an empty stomach?

00:09:08.320 --> 00:09:10.364
Is it okay for the bar to smell like food?

00:09:10.447 --> 00:09:11.907
Who cares? It's my bar.

00:09:17.245 --> 00:09:20.290
Jeez, I should just run a restaurant
instead of a bar.

00:09:20.874 --> 00:09:24.252
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:09:31.093 --> 00:09:32.052
VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION

00:09:32.135 --> 00:09:35.389
I got approval
to reopen the Kim Yun-ji case.

00:09:36.431 --> 00:09:37.516
Really?

00:09:37.599 --> 00:09:39.017
Yes!

00:09:40.435 --> 00:09:41.978
But if we strike out again,

00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:44.564
I'll have to resign.

00:09:47.192 --> 00:09:50.570
Treat everyone who was at Royal Auction
that night as a suspect,

00:09:50.654 --> 00:09:53.365
and investigate every single one of them.

00:09:54.241 --> 00:09:57.244
Then we need to get the VIP list first.

00:09:57.911 --> 00:09:59.037
I know someone who can help.

00:10:00.914 --> 00:10:01.873
PORTRAITS OF A WOMAN: SPECIAL EXHIBITION

00:10:01.957 --> 00:10:04.251
This special exhibition,
Portraits of a Woman,

00:10:04.334 --> 00:10:06.128
strives to capture
the artistic spirit of female artists

00:10:06.670 --> 00:10:09.172
who challenge life's injustices

00:10:09.256 --> 00:10:11.466
and defy conventional expectations
through their work.

00:10:12.259 --> 00:10:15.470
This piece attempts to subvert

00:10:15.554 --> 00:10:16.763
the traditional image of a seiren.

00:10:17.597 --> 00:10:21.351
It sheds the symbolism
of a witch who lures men to their deaths

00:10:21.435 --> 00:10:23.103
and instead portrays

00:10:23.186 --> 00:10:25.355
the modern femme fatale,

00:10:25.439 --> 00:10:27.399
a woman of undeniable allure

00:10:27.482 --> 00:10:30.527
who never loses her sense of agency.

00:10:31.570 --> 00:10:33.029
It sounds just like you, Ms. Han.

00:10:35.532 --> 00:10:38.118
It's good to see you looking well
despite what happened.

00:10:38.702 --> 00:10:41.580
I heard about your fiancé's accident.

00:10:41.663 --> 00:10:43.206
It must've been so hard for you.

00:10:47.002 --> 00:10:49.171
Thank you for your concern.

00:10:49.254 --> 00:10:51.465
Had I known,
I wouldn't have written about Ms. Kim.

00:10:52.757 --> 00:10:54.551
I had no idea it was a string of deaths.

00:11:01.641 --> 00:11:03.560
Shall we wrap it up, then?

00:11:03.643 --> 00:11:04.644
Sure.

00:11:04.728 --> 00:11:06.104
Thank you.

00:11:16.698 --> 00:11:18.825
I couldn't get anything out of Ms. Han.

00:11:19.784 --> 00:11:20.827
I figured as much.

00:11:24.539 --> 00:11:25.582
It's the annual advertising contract.

00:11:28.793 --> 00:11:29.961
Just give me some content,

00:11:30.545 --> 00:11:32.005
and I'll spin it into an amazing piece.

00:11:32.088 --> 00:11:34.090
THE CLIENT SHALL PAY THE SERVICE PROVIDER
A FEE OF 30,000,000 WON

00:11:34.174 --> 00:11:35.175
Would you look at that.

00:11:36.051 --> 00:11:37.719
This is a hefty invoice.

00:11:38.303 --> 00:11:39.471
Got anything juicier?

00:11:39.554 --> 00:11:40.805
Juicier?

00:11:40.889 --> 00:11:43.683
Gossip is only interesting
when it's ongoing.

00:11:45.977 --> 00:11:47.062
Something juicier, huh?

00:11:49.898 --> 00:11:50.982
Just you wait.

00:12:22.764 --> 00:12:24.474
This is the insurance policy
for the Stiller.

00:12:27.394 --> 00:12:29.688
Insurance documents
contain a lot of information

00:12:29.771 --> 00:12:33.400
about who took out policies
and the circumstances,

00:12:34.276 --> 00:12:35.819
including when, how, and why.

00:12:38.280 --> 00:12:41.449
Your family's case is too old,
and the insurance company is gone.

00:12:42.158 --> 00:12:43.326
Is that why you confessed?

00:12:44.661 --> 00:12:46.079
In the end,

00:12:47.205 --> 00:12:49.249
you won't find out anything.

00:12:50.458 --> 00:12:51.751
I'm the only one who knows the truth

00:12:52.877 --> 00:12:53.962
about that day.

00:12:56.464 --> 00:12:57.757
You wanted me to believe you.

00:13:00.969 --> 00:13:02.012
Or was that not the case?

00:13:25.076 --> 00:13:25.910
UNREAD MESSAGES

00:14:03.615 --> 00:14:05.075
Who are you?

00:14:06.534 --> 00:14:09.371
It's 45, Saebit-ro, Yeonho-gu,
Cheonin-si, Gyeonggi.

00:14:09.454 --> 00:14:10.664
Felix Storage.

00:14:11.247 --> 00:14:12.499
Come to this location.

00:14:12.582 --> 00:14:13.917
If you don't arrive within an hour,

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:15.919
the whole world will know your secret.

00:15:50.555 --> 00:15:52.140
I'm looking for this area.

00:16:05.737 --> 00:16:08.114
Can you tell me who left this here?

00:16:08.198 --> 00:16:10.325
I'm afraid I can't disclose that
due to security reasons.

00:16:31.846 --> 00:16:34.682
I'm with the person who came
from Royal Auction.

00:16:35.767 --> 00:16:36.810
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU SENIOR MANAGER CHA WOO-SEOK

00:16:40.355 --> 00:16:41.481
Thank you.

00:17:41.165 --> 00:17:46.296
Artwork and wine are kept
in a separate, secure area here,

00:17:46.379 --> 00:17:47.755
so you can check for yourself in a moment.

00:17:52.093 --> 00:17:53.803
This is a live CCTV feed.

00:17:53.887 --> 00:17:57.807
You can monitor the entrance and interior
of the storage facility around the clock.

00:19:14.467 --> 00:19:15.301
Watch out!

00:19:28.856 --> 00:19:29.732
Are you okay?

00:19:36.406 --> 00:19:37.365
Damn it.

00:19:44.956 --> 00:19:45.999
What…

00:20:06.686 --> 00:20:08.062
You're all set.

00:20:08.146 --> 00:20:10.314
I'll give you more hydrocolloid bandages.

00:20:10.398 --> 00:20:12.483
If it swells up,
replace it with a new one.

00:20:13.317 --> 00:20:14.277
Thank you.

00:20:15.403 --> 00:20:16.821
Does she not need to go to the hospital?

00:20:17.655 --> 00:20:18.948
It's just an abrasion,

00:20:19.032 --> 00:20:21.743
so if she keeps the bandage on,
it should heal without scarring.

00:20:27.248 --> 00:20:28.291
She's a former nurse.

00:20:29.083 --> 00:20:31.794
She's an expert,
so you don't need to worry.

00:20:33.504 --> 00:20:35.840
That's quite an unusual background
for a secretary.

00:20:38.134 --> 00:20:39.635
I specifically hired her

00:20:39.719 --> 00:20:42.930
because I'm still dealing
with the aftereffects of an accident.

00:21:01.699 --> 00:21:02.700
We can't disclose

00:21:02.784 --> 00:21:04.494
the storage owner's details
due to privacy reasons.

00:21:04.577 --> 00:21:06.204
This wasn't an accident.
It was intentional.

00:21:06.287 --> 00:21:07.663
A person got injured!

00:21:08.164 --> 00:21:09.499
Then call the police.

00:21:09.582 --> 00:21:11.042
If the police investigate,

00:21:11.125 --> 00:21:13.419
won't other customers' identities
get exposed too?

00:21:14.629 --> 00:21:17.548
If that's the case,
I'll have to reconsider my contract.

00:21:19.008 --> 00:21:19.926
Mr. Paek.

00:21:20.009 --> 00:21:23.346
If you just tell us the storage owner
and leave it at that,

00:21:24.222 --> 00:21:25.515
everyone comes out ahead.

00:22:05.263 --> 00:22:07.056
What brought you here

00:22:08.683 --> 00:22:10.017
at this particular time?

00:22:11.644 --> 00:22:15.356
I was considering signing with them
for a warehouse for our new venture.

00:22:16.107 --> 00:22:17.400
What brought you two here?

00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:21.320
We came because this is
one of our storage providers.

00:22:22.029 --> 00:22:24.448
Thank you for your help, Mr. Paek.

00:22:25.199 --> 00:22:26.450
Are you sure you're okay?

00:22:26.534 --> 00:22:27.702
Let me drive you back.

00:22:27.785 --> 00:22:29.036
It's okay.

00:22:29.704 --> 00:22:31.789
I still have some work to take care of.

00:22:33.040 --> 00:22:34.208
I'll drive her back,

00:22:34.292 --> 00:22:36.794
so just have your driver
bring Ms. Han's car around front.

00:22:39.881 --> 00:22:40.840
As you wish.

00:23:04.238 --> 00:23:05.531
Did you follow me?

00:23:05.615 --> 00:23:06.699
Why did you come here?

00:23:07.533 --> 00:23:08.993
Why did you go inside?

00:23:09.619 --> 00:23:10.786
You think this is a coincidence?

00:23:10.870 --> 00:23:12.622
Someone set a trap on purpose.

00:23:13.456 --> 00:23:15.291
How could you come here alone?

00:23:16.334 --> 00:23:17.919
You should've told me!

00:23:19.921 --> 00:23:22.590
Tell me what's going on so I can help you.

00:23:24.175 --> 00:23:25.051
Help?

00:23:26.260 --> 00:23:27.595
Don't you mean suspect?

00:23:28.971 --> 00:23:30.264
What if I'm concerned and not suspicious?

00:23:31.557 --> 00:23:32.892
You claim you killed your parents,

00:23:34.268 --> 00:23:36.270
yet I'm still searching for reasons
it wasn't you.

00:23:43.069 --> 00:23:44.111
Who is this person?

00:23:45.696 --> 00:23:47.198
Oh, that's Hwang Suk-ji.

00:23:47.281 --> 00:23:48.616
She's Ms. Han's friend,

00:23:48.699 --> 00:23:51.410
and she owns a bar near the company.

00:23:52.995 --> 00:23:55.289
-And who's this?
-That's Ko Sang-mi.

00:23:55.373 --> 00:23:56.207
She's an assistant manager.

00:23:56.832 --> 00:24:00.044
This is the person Ms. Kim Yun-ji
was last seen with that day.

00:24:07.718 --> 00:24:08.970
ROYAL AUCTION VIP NIGHT

00:24:09.053 --> 00:24:10.388
PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:24:10.471 --> 00:24:11.472
Right here.

00:24:12.348 --> 00:24:13.808
His name is Paek Jun-beom.

00:24:13.891 --> 00:24:16.102
He made a fortune with a start-up.

00:24:16.811 --> 00:24:20.189
He and Ms. Han
have been getting pretty cozy lately.

00:24:25.111 --> 00:24:25.987
But…

00:24:27.071 --> 00:24:28.406
I highly doubt it's anything serious.

00:24:28.489 --> 00:24:30.574
Why would someone running
a unicorn company go for someone like her?

00:24:32.660 --> 00:24:33.869
Oh, right.

00:24:33.953 --> 00:24:35.454
I find this one a bit off though.

00:24:40.501 --> 00:24:41.502
Mr. Do Eun-hyuk?

00:24:41.585 --> 00:24:42.420
Yes.

00:24:43.045 --> 00:24:45.298
There are rumors all over the company

00:24:45.381 --> 00:24:47.133
that he worships Ms. Han like a queen.

00:24:49.302 --> 00:24:51.887
I wouldn't have hired him
if I'd known they went to school together.

00:25:02.857 --> 00:25:05.943
Do Eun-hyuk was in Cheongun
on the day of Yoon Seung-jae's accident.

00:25:06.027 --> 00:25:08.863
He was also at the scene
when Kim Yun-ji died.

00:25:09.655 --> 00:25:12.116
And he was the one
who helped prove Han Seol-ah's alibi.

00:25:13.576 --> 00:25:16.829
Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk
working together as accomplices?

00:25:19.373 --> 00:25:21.167
That sounds totally plausible.

00:25:21.834 --> 00:25:22.960
If there was an accomplice,

00:25:23.836 --> 00:25:27.465
we could disprove Han Seol-ah's alibi
at the time of Kim Yun-ji's fall.

00:25:27.548 --> 00:25:29.842
If only we had one case to leverage

00:25:29.925 --> 00:25:32.678
before we bring in Do Eun-hyuk
for questioning.

00:25:32.762 --> 00:25:35.431
If the Kim Yun-ji case
seems like a dead end,

00:25:35.514 --> 00:25:36.599
we'll just find another way.

00:25:41.020 --> 00:25:42.980
Let's look into
Yoon Seung-jae's death case again.

00:25:52.239 --> 00:25:53.866
I thought they'd reveal themselves

00:25:53.949 --> 00:25:55.701
if I came alone.

00:25:58.371 --> 00:25:59.914
This isn't something you can handle alone.

00:26:00.498 --> 00:26:02.750
They lured you out here
and put you in danger,

00:26:03.834 --> 00:26:06.087
but their plans went sideways
because I showed up.

00:26:06.170 --> 00:26:07.588
Do you really think

00:26:08.798 --> 00:26:10.508
Mr. Paek is behind all this?

00:26:29.860 --> 00:26:31.779
I saw someone suspicious
in the storage facility.

00:26:32.738 --> 00:26:35.366
Then Paek Jun-beom came running
as if he had been waiting.

00:26:40.746 --> 00:26:42.123
Then do you think

00:26:42.998 --> 00:26:44.667
he might be watching us from somewhere
right now?

00:27:28.752 --> 00:27:29.795
Let's go in together.

00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:33.299
Let's see how they react.

00:28:13.088 --> 00:28:15.508
There's only water and alcohol here.

00:28:15.591 --> 00:28:16.425
Take your pick.

00:28:19.720 --> 00:28:20.721
I'll have what you're having.

00:28:43.285 --> 00:28:44.954
I noticed this logo on his business card.

00:28:45.454 --> 00:28:46.497
Does it have a special meaning?

00:28:47.206 --> 00:28:50.584
Anyway, it's a shame
that you can't trust people.

00:28:56.298 --> 00:28:57.132
Is this

00:28:58.592 --> 00:28:59.426
a common wine?

00:29:02.429 --> 00:29:03.264
No.

00:29:03.347 --> 00:29:05.975
He designed the label himself,

00:29:06.058 --> 00:29:07.977
so it was sold exclusively
at the restaurant.

00:29:08.978 --> 00:29:11.063
I saw the same wine
at Paek Jun-beom's place,

00:29:11.647 --> 00:29:13.399
which means
he definitely visited the restaurant.

00:29:39.133 --> 00:29:40.259
Aren't you afraid of me?

00:29:42.678 --> 00:29:44.471
I could be lying to you

00:29:45.889 --> 00:29:48.017
after killing all those men.

00:29:52.521 --> 00:29:53.689
I suppose so.

00:29:56.025 --> 00:29:58.110
And I told you I started the fire.

00:29:59.862 --> 00:30:01.030
Those words stuck with me…

00:30:02.698 --> 00:30:03.699
and came across differently.

00:30:07.911 --> 00:30:09.246
It was as if you wanted me

00:30:10.789 --> 00:30:12.041
to see the hidden truth.

00:30:18.881 --> 00:30:20.466
Usually, it's the adults
who create tragedies,

00:30:21.925 --> 00:30:23.052
not the children.

00:30:30.059 --> 00:30:31.226
It was my choice.

00:30:43.572 --> 00:30:45.991
People who have hit rock bottom know

00:30:47.159 --> 00:30:48.494
that misfortune

00:30:48.577 --> 00:30:52.039
has a way of going after those
who have nothing.

00:30:52.748 --> 00:30:55.876
The loan shark debt my father owed
kept snowballing,

00:30:56.460 --> 00:30:58.253
and there was no way out

00:30:59.546 --> 00:31:00.506
until he died.

00:31:02.633 --> 00:31:03.634
Go see a movie.

00:31:05.302 --> 00:31:06.929
You said you wanted to.

00:31:11.350 --> 00:31:12.393
See you later.

00:31:15.562 --> 00:31:16.397
One day,

00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:19.775
my mom forced me to go out
and see a movie.

00:31:24.655 --> 00:31:25.864
Something didn't feel right.

00:31:25.948 --> 00:31:27.241
DUMARI CHICKEN

00:31:29.451 --> 00:31:31.370
I used the money
to buy fried chicken back home instead.

00:31:35.416 --> 00:31:38.502
But by then,
my parents had already taken pesticide…

00:31:42.798 --> 00:31:44.633
and there was gasoline all over the floor.

00:31:48.470 --> 00:31:51.557
I knew they were trying to stage the fire
as an accident.

00:32:17.958 --> 00:32:20.002
I was going to die with them…

00:32:23.797 --> 00:32:25.174
but I failed.

00:32:33.140 --> 00:32:36.477
And I ended up alone in hell.

00:32:44.485 --> 00:32:45.736
I found out later

00:32:46.820 --> 00:32:48.781
that my father wanted to use
the death benefit…

00:32:50.699 --> 00:32:52.743
to pay off the debt.

00:32:54.536 --> 00:32:56.580
When my mom found out,

00:32:56.663 --> 00:32:58.290
she decided to die with him.

00:32:59.917 --> 00:33:01.126
I'm alive today…

00:33:03.003 --> 00:33:04.880
at the cost of their lives.

00:33:09.301 --> 00:33:10.761
I'm a terrible daughter.

00:33:12.471 --> 00:33:15.015
You only wanted to ease
your parents' suffering,

00:33:16.350 --> 00:33:18.143
but the world was so cruel

00:33:19.603 --> 00:33:20.687
that it made a child want to die.

00:33:57.474 --> 00:33:58.392
Don't hold it in.

00:34:02.312 --> 00:34:03.438
It's okay to cry.

00:34:27.588 --> 00:34:30.132
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:34:33.343 --> 00:34:34.761
The cause of death was drowning,

00:34:34.845 --> 00:34:36.972
and his injuries were sustained
after he fell into the water.

00:34:37.055 --> 00:34:38.223
YACHT REPAIRED THE DAY BEFORE THE ACCIDENT

00:34:38.307 --> 00:34:41.101
Records show that the yacht was repaired
the day before the accident.

00:34:41.685 --> 00:34:43.812
Yes, Cheongun Police checked out the place

00:34:43.896 --> 00:34:45.480
but didn't find anything unusual.

00:34:47.941 --> 00:34:49.067
Things could be different at the scene.

00:34:49.818 --> 00:34:50.777
Let's check it out.

00:34:53.822 --> 00:34:54.823
Hello.

00:34:56.408 --> 00:34:57.576
Oh, Sang-mi.

00:34:58.368 --> 00:35:01.538
You're in charge of managing
our off-site storage providers, right?

00:35:01.622 --> 00:35:02.748
Yes.

00:35:02.831 --> 00:35:05.292
Please send me that list right now.

00:35:05.375 --> 00:35:07.085
I'll do that right away.

00:35:12.466 --> 00:35:15.302
OFF-SITE STORAGE PROVIDER CONTRACT STATUS

00:35:23.477 --> 00:35:24.519
Come to this location.

00:35:33.195 --> 00:35:35.072
Do you need to contact a provider?

00:35:36.782 --> 00:35:37.950
Oh.

00:35:38.033 --> 00:35:39.952
Can we find out what pieces

00:35:40.035 --> 00:35:42.663
are being stored at Felix Storage?

00:35:42.746 --> 00:35:46.083
They blocked it off
for Chair Kim's personal use.

00:35:46.166 --> 00:35:48.877
We signed a contract, but I don't think
anything has been stored there yet.

00:35:50.420 --> 00:35:53.548
-Is that so?
-I haven't received any official orders.

00:35:54.299 --> 00:35:55.509
All right.

00:36:20.951 --> 00:36:22.327
You're here.

00:36:23.328 --> 00:36:24.830
Is this going to Hannam-dong?

00:36:25.622 --> 00:36:26.707
Yeah.

00:36:26.790 --> 00:36:30.544
She spent three billion won
on random paintings,

00:36:30.627 --> 00:36:32.879
so I'm sure she's waiting eagerly.

00:36:32.963 --> 00:36:35.257
It's about time I send her an invitation.

00:36:36.800 --> 00:36:38.885
Now that she's getting
one of your kimchi jars,

00:36:38.969 --> 00:36:42.180
she can finally buy the paintings
she really wants.

00:36:42.264 --> 00:36:43.181
That's right.

00:36:44.016 --> 00:36:47.894
It's the same as spending
tens of millions of won

00:36:47.978 --> 00:36:49.479
to be able to purchase
a luxury bag like that.

00:36:52.441 --> 00:36:55.819
People take such pride in being chosen

00:36:55.902 --> 00:36:59.072
that they get carried away spending money.

00:37:03.368 --> 00:37:06.663
How did you know
she'd spend three billion won?

00:37:08.874 --> 00:37:10.792
There was a look in her eye.

00:37:11.501 --> 00:37:14.337
People can't hide their greed, you know.

00:37:22.387 --> 00:37:24.681
I see that kind of look sometimes.

00:37:27.017 --> 00:37:27.893
Right.

00:37:29.019 --> 00:37:30.729
This is really nothing special.

00:37:31.480 --> 00:37:34.232
I don't know why people make such a fuss
over not receiving this.

00:37:35.108 --> 00:37:35.942
Goodness.

00:37:51.208 --> 00:37:54.336
I emailed you the media art video
for the upcoming exhibition.

00:37:54.419 --> 00:37:56.171
Please take a look.

00:37:56.254 --> 00:37:57.172
All right.

00:37:57.756 --> 00:37:58.840
Did it turn out okay?

00:37:58.924 --> 00:38:01.468
Nothing appeals to me these days.

00:38:02.052 --> 00:38:04.513
It's a reinterpretation
of Andy Warhol's work,

00:38:04.596 --> 00:38:06.556
and it shows the bold energy
of an emerging artist.

00:38:06.640 --> 00:38:08.141
It's a bit provocative,

00:38:08.225 --> 00:38:09.810
but it stays in line with current trends.

00:38:11.978 --> 00:38:13.063
Is that so?

00:38:22.531 --> 00:38:23.615
Let's see here.

00:38:29.162 --> 00:38:30.997
I like the color scheme.

00:38:32.958 --> 00:38:35.127
The visual transitions are a bit fast.

00:38:36.711 --> 00:38:39.756
Young artists these days
have some really interesting ideas.

00:38:41.091 --> 00:38:42.092
I'm glad to hear that.

00:38:42.175 --> 00:38:44.803
I'll make some adjustments
based on your feedback.

00:38:44.886 --> 00:38:46.221
All right.

00:39:17.169 --> 00:39:18.378
Who is it?

00:39:18.461 --> 00:39:20.005
I'm from Royal Auction.

00:39:40.984 --> 00:39:42.110
The Katarina?

00:39:42.903 --> 00:39:44.696
It had a lot of minor issues.

00:39:45.947 --> 00:39:47.741
As big as they are,

00:39:47.824 --> 00:39:50.035
yachts can be
surprisingly high-maintenance.

00:39:51.494 --> 00:39:54.664
Let's see, the Katarina…

00:39:54.748 --> 00:39:56.082
Here it is.

00:39:57.042 --> 00:39:58.501
BOAT MAINTENANCE ESTIMATE

00:40:00.378 --> 00:40:02.923
There was a loose connection
between the engine and starter wire.

00:40:03.465 --> 00:40:04.799
Think of it as a couple

00:40:05.508 --> 00:40:06.927
on the brink of divorce.

00:40:07.636 --> 00:40:08.803
The engine has trouble starting

00:40:09.512 --> 00:40:12.098
and sometimes just shuts off.

00:40:12.974 --> 00:40:14.768
-Then what--
-But the thing is,

00:40:15.477 --> 00:40:17.479
I'm positive that I fixed all that.

00:40:19.314 --> 00:40:20.982
There was nothing wrong with the yacht.

00:40:21.066 --> 00:40:22.859
My pride is on the line here.

00:40:22.943 --> 00:40:24.778
I'm more than capable of fixing this.

00:40:24.861 --> 00:40:28.156
Did Mr. Yoon Seung-jae
mention anything that day?

00:40:28.782 --> 00:40:31.993
I think his friend came instead that day.

00:40:32.577 --> 00:40:34.287
I think he said Mr. Yoon was busy
or something.

00:40:35.288 --> 00:40:36.498
His friend?

00:40:38.208 --> 00:40:39.209
Was it a man?

00:40:39.834 --> 00:40:42.796
Yes, they came here together
every now and then.

00:40:47.759 --> 00:40:48.885
Was it this person?

00:40:52.222 --> 00:40:53.223
Was it?

00:40:53.723 --> 00:40:55.642
I think it was him.

00:40:56.559 --> 00:40:57.477
Yes.

00:41:01.106 --> 00:41:03.525
Can you make repairs
without the owner present?

00:41:04.401 --> 00:41:06.903
Well, I did it because he had the key.

00:41:08.238 --> 00:41:09.114
The key?

00:41:09.698 --> 00:41:12.284
The key to the Katarina.

00:41:26.089 --> 00:41:27.215
Are you leaving early?

00:41:27.299 --> 00:41:29.467
See? I told you not to come to work.

00:41:30.510 --> 00:41:32.304
Eat this and get some sleep.

00:41:33.722 --> 00:41:35.515
Or I can take you to the hospital.

00:41:35.598 --> 00:41:37.225
There's no time. I have to get going.

00:41:37.309 --> 00:41:38.435
Go where?

00:41:38.518 --> 00:41:39.853
I thought you were heading home.

00:41:39.936 --> 00:41:42.147
There's a problem with the catalog I sent,

00:41:42.230 --> 00:41:44.065
so I have to go to the print shop.

00:41:44.149 --> 00:41:45.275
But the Auction Team…

00:41:46.985 --> 00:41:48.486
Did Han Seol-ah tell you to go?

00:41:48.570 --> 00:41:50.322
The Auction Team has a heavy workload.

00:41:50.405 --> 00:41:51.781
Are you an idiot?

00:41:51.865 --> 00:41:53.575
Why do you do everything she asks?

00:41:53.658 --> 00:41:55.660
My photos are in that catalog.

00:41:56.870 --> 00:41:57.704
I'm okay.

00:41:58.288 --> 00:41:59.664
I'll go home afterward.

00:42:54.094 --> 00:42:58.390
One of you will stand next to me
at the next major auction.

00:42:58.473 --> 00:42:59.474
It's been decided

00:42:59.557 --> 00:43:01.810
that the associate auctioneer
will be selected internally,

00:43:01.893 --> 00:43:03.019
so give it your best effort.

00:43:04.187 --> 00:43:05.230
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

00:43:14.864 --> 00:43:15.698
You can leave now.

00:43:33.216 --> 00:43:34.050
Lunch?

00:43:34.717 --> 00:43:35.552
Have you eaten?

00:43:36.136 --> 00:43:36.970
Not yet.

00:43:37.053 --> 00:43:39.139
Shall we go have lunch, then?

00:43:51.151 --> 00:43:52.944
I'm telling you, something's up.

00:43:53.027 --> 00:43:53.987
No way.

00:43:54.070 --> 00:43:57.282
Are you saying
there's something between them?

00:43:57.907 --> 00:43:59.492
That's not like Ms. Han.

00:43:59.576 --> 00:44:01.077
There was a look in their eyes.

00:44:01.161 --> 00:44:02.829
It was full of romance.

00:44:02.912 --> 00:44:05.039
And they went out for lunch on their own.

00:44:05.123 --> 00:44:07.625
Oh, my. Maybe they're already dating.

00:44:08.668 --> 00:44:09.502
Hey.

00:44:09.586 --> 00:44:10.503
What about us?

00:44:12.755 --> 00:44:13.923
Darn it, I was saving it.

00:44:17.302 --> 00:44:18.928
You want one? Here you go.

00:44:19.012 --> 00:44:20.763
As usual, this is getting me
through the day.

00:44:34.569 --> 00:44:36.070
Complimentary drinks for friends.

00:44:36.154 --> 00:44:38.072
They say the more you fight,
the closer you get.

00:44:38.156 --> 00:44:39.616
It's nice to see you two getting along.

00:44:40.909 --> 00:44:42.869
Thanks. Can you leave us to talk?

00:44:42.952 --> 00:44:44.370
Oh, sure.

00:44:59.344 --> 00:45:02.305
By this time tomorrow,
even the cleaning staff at Royal Auction

00:45:02.388 --> 00:45:03.890
will probably recognize you

00:45:04.891 --> 00:45:06.226
as the star of the gossip.

00:45:06.809 --> 00:45:07.810
No way.

00:45:20.740 --> 00:45:22.116
It'll certainly be effective.

00:45:25.453 --> 00:45:26.621
Tell me everything.

00:45:27.288 --> 00:45:29.541
Anything that could be connected
to Paek Jun-beom.

00:45:32.835 --> 00:45:35.755
I first met him at an auction preview

00:45:36.297 --> 00:45:38.216
about a week before Ms. Kim's accident.

00:45:39.217 --> 00:45:40.301
Are you sure about that?

00:45:40.802 --> 00:45:41.636
Yes.

00:45:41.719 --> 00:45:43.429
I'd never seen him before that.

00:45:46.975 --> 00:45:47.809
But for some reason,

00:45:48.893 --> 00:45:51.062
I got the feeling he already knew me.

00:45:51.938 --> 00:45:53.523
I can't explain it,

00:45:55.275 --> 00:45:56.859
but it felt like
he looked right through me.

00:45:59.195 --> 00:46:01.030
Chances are, he already knew you.

00:46:02.198 --> 00:46:05.285
He probably kept tabs on you for a while
before approaching.

00:46:07.453 --> 00:46:08.580
But why?

00:46:12.500 --> 00:46:14.294
If he's the one who killed those men,

00:46:15.336 --> 00:46:16.671
there's only one reason.

00:46:20.550 --> 00:46:21.718
He wants you.

00:47:02.592 --> 00:47:04.594
HAN SEOL-AH(28).M4A

00:47:04.677 --> 00:47:05.595
Seol-ah.

00:47:06.554 --> 00:47:07.388
Where are you right now?

00:47:08.514 --> 00:47:09.349
Why?

00:47:10.642 --> 00:47:11.559
Seung-jae…

00:47:13.061 --> 00:47:14.228
was in an accident.

00:47:15.688 --> 00:47:16.564
Can you…

00:47:17.732 --> 00:47:19.359
Can you come to the dock right now?

00:47:22.695 --> 00:47:24.656
"Can you come to the dock right now?"

00:47:25.239 --> 00:47:26.491
The investigation report

00:47:26.574 --> 00:47:28.701
states that Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk
arrived at the scene

00:47:28.785 --> 00:47:30.620
less than an hour after the police called.

00:47:31.329 --> 00:47:34.707
By the way,
why wasn't that logged as evidence?

00:47:36.376 --> 00:47:38.127
I discovered it late.

00:47:38.211 --> 00:47:39.712
Did you report it to me?

00:47:40.505 --> 00:47:41.631
Of course.

00:47:47.053 --> 00:47:47.887
YOUR HOME

00:47:47.970 --> 00:47:48.846
Look here.

00:47:49.764 --> 00:47:52.433
This is usually
where the CEO's photo goes,

00:47:52.517 --> 00:47:53.518
but it's empty.

00:47:53.601 --> 00:47:56.896
This means the bastard
is insecure about his looks.

00:47:56.979 --> 00:47:57.939
But check this out.

00:48:00.817 --> 00:48:02.610
He's unexpectedly
and insanely good-looking.

00:48:03.236 --> 00:48:05.780
I mean, it's totally unfair.

00:48:05.863 --> 00:48:08.449
He's good-looking, tall, well-educated,

00:48:08.533 --> 00:48:10.660
and filthy rich from making an app.

00:48:11.953 --> 00:48:13.413
You should've made an app too.

00:48:13.496 --> 00:48:14.664
I know, right?

00:48:14.747 --> 00:48:16.958
Why am I only smart
when it comes to bad stuff?

00:48:17.041 --> 00:48:18.876
Hey, zoom in on that photo.

00:48:19.585 --> 00:48:21.212
-Which one?
-This one.

00:48:21.295 --> 00:48:22.588
-This one?
-Yeah.

00:48:28.261 --> 00:48:29.178
"OnWorld"?

00:48:29.762 --> 00:48:31.764
On the 14th in Raqqa, Syria,

00:48:31.848 --> 00:48:34.600
a terrorist attack was carried out
by an armed group called IS,

00:48:34.684 --> 00:48:37.395
claiming the life of a Korean aid worker

00:48:37.478 --> 00:48:39.063
and adding to the grief of this tragedy.

00:48:40.231 --> 00:48:42.442
Lee Su-ho died in Syria,
and he was also with OnWorld.

00:48:59.292 --> 00:49:00.960
ONWORLD VOLUNTEER WORK PHOTO BOOK

00:49:06.382 --> 00:49:07.717
I'm sorry for the wait.

00:49:08.968 --> 00:49:11.596
It took a while to find these.

00:49:11.679 --> 00:49:12.597
That's okay.

00:49:12.680 --> 00:49:13.556
Please take a seat.

00:49:18.186 --> 00:49:21.981
I don't see a Paek Jun-beom
in our personnel records,

00:49:22.064 --> 00:49:26.068
but if he was wearing our vest,
he was probably a volunteer.

00:49:27.069 --> 00:49:28.946
-A volunteer?
-Yes.

00:49:29.030 --> 00:49:31.783
We have so many one-off volunteer events
that it's hard to keep track.

00:49:31.866 --> 00:49:34.202
Oh, but I can ask
the volunteer group for you.

00:49:35.203 --> 00:49:36.037
Thank you.

00:49:36.120 --> 00:49:39.123
And as for Mr. Lee Su-ho,

00:49:39.624 --> 00:49:41.334
he was our employee.

00:49:44.295 --> 00:49:47.173
I heard he got into an accident in Syria,

00:49:47.256 --> 00:49:48.925
but that happened before I started here.

00:49:49.926 --> 00:49:52.595
Is there anyone who knew him well?

00:49:54.096 --> 00:49:57.850
The relief team leader, Mr. Lee Kwang-jin,
probably knew him well

00:49:57.934 --> 00:49:59.936
since he's been on every overseas mission.

00:50:01.187 --> 00:50:03.523
Then he might remember Paek Jun-beom.

00:50:03.606 --> 00:50:05.983
I suppose so if they went together.

00:50:06.067 --> 00:50:07.068
Is he here right now?

00:50:07.902 --> 00:50:10.154
He's currently in Laos on business,

00:50:10.238 --> 00:50:11.489
but he'll be back soon.

00:50:16.828 --> 00:50:19.205
PERSONNEL FILE
NAME: LEE SU-HO

00:50:24.794 --> 00:50:25.628
Right here.

00:50:28.381 --> 00:50:30.758
We're focusing on the accomplice angle

00:50:30.842 --> 00:50:33.177
and identifying potential suspects
among Han Seol-ah's associates.

00:50:34.387 --> 00:50:37.265
I'm here to ask for your cooperation
with the investigation.

00:50:37.849 --> 00:50:39.392
It's your request,
so of course we'll cooperate.

00:50:40.268 --> 00:50:42.395
I can give you the records of her parents.

00:50:43.062 --> 00:50:44.021
What else do you need?

00:50:46.190 --> 00:50:48.526
For now, we need the SIU to stay back

00:50:48.609 --> 00:50:50.194
and let the police handle everything.

00:50:54.323 --> 00:50:55.741
Where have you been?

00:50:56.325 --> 00:50:58.411
-What is it?
-Detective Gong is here.

00:50:59.161 --> 00:51:00.162
She's over there.

00:51:04.458 --> 00:51:06.502
We'll request your cooperation
in the joint investigation

00:51:06.586 --> 00:51:08.337
once we find Kim Yun-ji's killer.

00:51:09.797 --> 00:51:11.299
That's fine by us.

00:51:19.807 --> 00:51:21.392
Why are you going this far?

00:51:24.312 --> 00:51:26.772
Do you have any idea what I did
to cover up that burner phone?

00:51:29.233 --> 00:51:31.027
Do you really believe Han Seol-ah?

00:51:31.527 --> 00:51:33.863
She received her parents'
insurance payout.

00:51:33.946 --> 00:51:35.531
It was a joint suicide.

00:51:36.115 --> 00:51:38.451
The family tried to die together,
but Han Seol-ah survived.

00:51:39.035 --> 00:51:41.370
She was only 15 years old
when she went through that.

00:51:45.708 --> 00:51:46.584
That woman…

00:51:48.002 --> 00:51:49.295
is just a victim.

00:51:49.378 --> 00:51:52.256
Are you sure your emotions
aren't keeping you from seeing the truth?

00:52:39.637 --> 00:52:40.596
Syria…

00:53:01.826 --> 00:53:03.911
BOAT MAINTENANCE ESTIMATE

00:53:04.495 --> 00:53:05.413
I did this…

00:53:07.248 --> 00:53:08.582
because Seol-ah asked me to.

00:53:10.001 --> 00:53:12.128
She was worried because the engine
wouldn't start properly,

00:53:13.045 --> 00:53:14.714
so she asked me to get it repaired…

00:53:16.757 --> 00:53:18.801
since Seung-jae was too busy
to take care of it himself.

00:53:19.885 --> 00:53:21.512
The mechanic repaired everything
without any problems.

00:53:21.595 --> 00:53:23.305
And the accident happened
the next day, correct?

00:53:25.683 --> 00:53:26.726
Who gave you the key?

00:53:29.145 --> 00:53:30.062
Seol-ah.

00:53:32.648 --> 00:53:35.109
I don't think
I would've wanted to do such a favor.

00:53:36.610 --> 00:53:37.528
Mr. Do Eun-hyuk.

00:53:38.320 --> 00:53:42.241
It seems like Han Seol-ah
always comes first in everything you do.

00:53:50.833 --> 00:53:52.334
SEOL-AH

00:53:55.212 --> 00:53:57.089
Go ahead and answer.

00:54:07.433 --> 00:54:09.185
SEOL-AH

00:54:16.942 --> 00:54:17.902
Is there a problem?

00:54:19.612 --> 00:54:20.780
No.

00:54:21.906 --> 00:54:22.740
There's no problem.

00:54:30.873 --> 00:54:32.833
MISSED CALL
SEOL-AH

00:54:35.377 --> 00:54:39.799
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:54:40.883 --> 00:54:43.260
This is Lee Kwang-jin from OnWorld.

00:54:43.844 --> 00:54:45.596
I heard you were looking for me.

00:54:45.679 --> 00:54:46.806
Hello, sir.

00:54:47.306 --> 00:54:49.683
I'm investigating
Mr. Lee Su-ho's accident, and--

00:54:49.767 --> 00:54:50.643
Su-ho

00:54:51.310 --> 00:54:53.270
died because of Han Seol-ah.

00:54:55.648 --> 00:54:57.650
I'm catching a flight back to Korea,

00:54:57.733 --> 00:54:59.235
so I'll explain everything when I arrive.

00:55:36.480 --> 00:55:37.481
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin?

00:55:38.983 --> 00:55:40.025
Yes.

00:55:42.862 --> 00:55:44.196
I'm Cha Woo-seok. We talked on the phone.

00:56:33.370 --> 00:56:34.205
Jun-beom?

00:56:34.955 --> 00:56:36.248
Of course, I remember him.

00:56:37.333 --> 00:56:40.252
He started volunteering for OnWorld
in college.

00:56:41.378 --> 00:56:43.297
Even though he came
from a well-off family,

00:56:43.380 --> 00:56:46.217
he really cared about the underprivileged.

00:56:46.300 --> 00:56:48.093
Did he also volunteer overseas?

00:56:48.594 --> 00:56:49.595
Yes.

00:56:49.678 --> 00:56:52.139
He even took time off from school to help.

00:57:01.106 --> 00:57:03.025
If it hadn't been
for that incident in Syria…

00:57:04.193 --> 00:57:05.152
Syria?

00:57:06.278 --> 00:57:07.863
Was he with Lee Su-ho?

01:00:00.494 --> 01:00:02.037
Do you remember

01:00:03.122 --> 01:00:03.956
anything at all?

01:00:04.039 --> 01:00:05.040
It was my fault.

01:00:05.124 --> 01:00:06.625
What if there's another accomplice?

01:00:07.251 --> 01:00:10.045
Someone with money, time, and the means.

01:00:10.129 --> 01:00:11.255
I've seen him before.

01:00:11.922 --> 01:00:13.382
If you've lost everything,

01:00:13.465 --> 01:00:17.344
you've got nothing left to lose
and nothing to fear.

01:00:17.845 --> 01:00:19.054
This accident happened

01:00:19.763 --> 01:00:22.015
while I was tracking down a suspect.

01:00:22.099 --> 01:00:24.226
What if I just use you and walk away?

01:00:24.309 --> 01:00:25.561
I don't care.

01:00:26.812 --> 01:00:28.480
Go ahead and use me.

01:00:30.774 --> 01:00:32.776
Subtitle: Jenny Kim